01:08:16.210 --> 01:08:20.250
And I wonder if you can comment
on that and on the current work

01:08:20.250 --> 01:08:22.290
being done in low
income settings

01:08:22.290 --> 01:08:25.379
on this type of microbiome
simplification work.

01:08:25.379 --> 01:08:25.920
- Absolutely.

01:08:25.920 --> 01:08:28.020
So, excellent questions.

01:08:28.020 --> 01:08:30.510
I think fundamentally
our microbiomes

01:08:30.510 --> 01:08:34.770
are great reflections of how
we experience our environment.

01:08:34.770 --> 01:08:36.310
I'll take your last
question first,

01:08:36.310 --> 01:08:38.340
which is this
question of studies

01:08:38.340 --> 01:08:40.050
in low and middle
income countries,

01:08:40.050 --> 01:08:42.810
and countries that are
currently undergoing

01:08:42.810 --> 01:08:44.580
rapid industrialization.

01:08:44.580 --> 01:08:46.229
There have been
very limited studies

01:08:46.229 --> 01:08:48.210
on the microbiome of
individuals outside

01:08:48.210 --> 01:08:50.100
of high income countries,
and indeed, outside

01:08:50.100 --> 01:08:51.979
of the US and Western Europe.

01:08:51.979 --> 01:08:53.729
And so this is an
area of much need.

01:08:53.729 --> 01:08:56.250
We don't have adequate
reference databases

01:08:56.250 --> 01:08:59.340
that tell us what the microbiome
of the vast majority of people

01:08:59.340 --> 01:09:00.761
in the world look like.

01:09:00.761 --> 01:09:02.760
The studies that have
been done have pretty much

01:09:02.760 --> 01:09:05.520
been done in small
tribes, often that

01:09:05.520 --> 01:09:08.100
are living in subsistence
farming communities,

01:09:08.100 --> 01:09:10.040
or in hunter
gatherer communities.

01:09:10.040 --> 01:09:12.210
There it's been
demonstrated that at least

01:09:12.210 --> 01:09:15.770
at the simplistic taxonomic
level, meaning who's there,

01:09:15.770 --> 01:09:19.260
the microbiomes are quite a
bit more complex than our own.

01:09:19.260 --> 01:09:21.779
Suggesting that Western
diet, you know the Happy Meal

01:09:21.779 --> 01:09:24.660
lifestyle, may be
compromising the complexity

01:09:24.660 --> 01:09:26.580
of our microbiomes.

01:09:26.580 --> 01:09:29.250
To your point about, will
we ever get to the point

01:09:29.250 --> 01:09:31.200
where we can measure
microbiomes and actually

01:09:31.200 --> 01:09:33.990
be able to predict
disease susceptibility?

01:09:33.990 --> 01:09:36.000
I think we can
absolutely get there.

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:39.930
I think we need to do two things
to achieve that, in addition

01:09:39.930 --> 01:09:42.930
to collecting data from
countries outside of those

01:09:42.930 --> 01:09:44.819
where our data are
overrepresented.

01:09:44.819 --> 01:09:47.850
One is collecting very high
quality clinical phenotype

01:09:47.850 --> 01:09:48.479
data.

01:09:48.479 --> 01:09:50.670
So whenever we collect
someone's stool sample,

01:09:50.670 --> 01:09:54.330
it's absolutely critical
that we collect information

01:09:54.330 --> 01:09:57.900
about, for example,
serology, disease history,

01:09:57.900 --> 01:10:00.480
migration, lifestyle.

01:10:00.480 --> 01:10:02.550
Secondarily, I think
we need to be committed

01:10:02.550 --> 01:10:04.260
to measuring what matters.

01:10:04.260 --> 01:10:08.400
And in our field we've been
very reliant upon measuring

01:10:08.400 --> 01:10:13.140
taxonomy, meaning who's there,
which genus, which species.

01:10:13.140 --> 01:10:15.450
As I showed you, these
genomes can evolve.

01:10:15.450 --> 01:10:16.890
And so maybe we
need to think more

01:10:16.890 --> 01:10:21.240
about measuring elements of
the microbiota that actually

01:10:21.240 --> 01:10:24.030
lead to functions, and
measuring what matters.

01:10:24.030 --> 01:10:27.360
Maybe we need to measure
what these microbes make

01:10:27.360 --> 01:10:29.290
or how they're
changing over time.

01:10:29.290 --> 01:10:29.790
- Right.

01:10:29.790 --> 01:10:30.290
Thank you.

01:10:30.290 --> 01:10:33.750
Or think about antimicrobial
resistance plasmids and things

01:10:33.750 --> 01:10:35.130
like this.

01:10:35.130 --> 01:10:37.802
So Jess, I'll move to you.

