01:10:57.330 --> 01:10:59.370
that we have not yet seen?

01:10:59.370 --> 01:11:01.290
Do you think that's reasonable?

01:11:01.290 --> 01:11:03.150
Or you think it's
limited to things

01:11:03.150 --> 01:11:06.540
that we already understand?

01:11:06.540 --> 01:11:09.490
- I think that it's
challenging to look

01:11:09.490 --> 01:11:11.890
for what you don't know.

01:11:11.890 --> 01:11:16.070
But I do think that
once an emergence is

01:11:16.070 --> 01:11:18.185
suspected that's where
the power of serology

01:11:18.185 --> 01:11:19.060
might come into play.

01:11:19.060 --> 01:11:21.680
Because quite often
many of the pathogens--

01:11:21.680 --> 01:11:23.560
we heard a lot about
this this morning.

01:11:23.560 --> 01:11:27.660
Many pathogens can have
asymptomatic infections

01:11:27.660 --> 01:11:29.770
and so you might have
no idea of the scope,

01:11:29.770 --> 01:11:32.200
particularly given uncertainty
in reporting systems.

01:11:32.200 --> 01:11:36.810
But if you happen to have a
blood bank in northern Brazil

01:11:36.810 --> 01:11:40.060
or other locations where
you suspected circulation,

01:11:40.060 --> 01:11:42.070
you would have a
way to ground truth

01:11:42.070 --> 01:11:44.410
that the way to understand
what might be going on.

01:11:44.410 --> 01:11:45.880
- Yeah, and for Ebola too.

01:11:45.880 --> 01:11:46.910
- And for Ebola too.

01:11:46.910 --> 01:11:50.260
I think there's a lot of
interesting questions about how

01:11:50.260 --> 01:11:54.760
whether our evolutionary ecology
theory could actually take us

01:11:54.760 --> 01:11:56.830
towards thinking a little
bit more about what

01:11:56.830 --> 01:12:00.190
would emerge where, but I think
that's at a very early stage

01:12:00.190 --> 01:12:02.260
in the science still.

